r being overly simplistic,\nwhereby the discipline relies on models of intermediate complexity that are\nusable by general ecologists, but grounded in well-developed statistical\npractice and efficient to fit to large data sets.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 24 Mar 2016 10:30:20 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 3 Sep 2016 18:51:40 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 30 Jan 2017 08:15:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-01-31"}
